{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":71069,"duration_api_ms":85107,"num_turns":4,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"a83a3d6e-b84f-4a3a-a7ed-0c74dbfddf45","total_cost_usd":0.2936854,"usage":{"input_tokens":821,"cache_creation_input_tokens":24777,"cache_read_input_tokens":77103,"output_tokens":2370,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":24777,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":24,"outputTokens":2838,"cacheReadInputTokens":72174,"cacheCreationInputTokens":12393,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.036922649999999994,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":821,"outputTokens":2370,"cacheReadInputTokens":77103,"cacheCreationInputTokens":24777,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.25676275,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"Independently verified all three amendments against the actual code in fs.rs and the test suite in service.rs. Amendment fr-18-fb16fc87 correctly identifies a real ordering dependency between safe_plan_hash_backfill (line 3395) and the outcome assignment (line 3396) that deserves documentation. Amendment fr-18-df19f0ba correctly identifies a misuse of AppError::CorruptRecord for an internal contract violation — the variant name misleads operational triage. Amendment fr-18-ffc497f2 contains a critical factual error: the test at lines 4727-4816 asserts that backfill SUCCEEDS at completion time (contrary to the amendment's claim of 'non-backfilling behavior'), and the code includes extensive inline documentation explaining the deliberate deviation for legacy entries.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-18-fb16fc87","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified in the code: safe_plan_hash_backfill is called on line 3395 while entry.outcome is still Running, and entry.outcome is only set to the terminal value on line 3396. The is_terminal() guard inside safe_plan_hash_backfill (line 2594) is therefore vacuous at this call site — it always sees Running and never short-circuits. This is correct behavior since this is the last chance to backfill before the entry becomes terminal, but if a future refactor moves safe_plan_hash_backfill after the outcome assignment, the is_terminal() guard would fire and silently suppress the backfill. A brief inline comment documenting this ordering invariant is low-cost, high-value, and prevents a subtle regression."},{"amendment_id":"fr-18-df19f0ba","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: the code at line 2839 uses AppError::CorruptRecord with a file path referencing 'milestones/{}/task-runs.ndjson' for what is actually a caller contract violation (run_id is Some but started_at is None). While the details string does say 'contract violation', the error variant name CorruptRecord and the included file path both point operators toward investigating on-disk data corruption rather than a bug in calling code. Monitoring and alerting systems typically dispatch on error variant, not detail text. Changing the variant to something like InternalContractViolation (or at least removing the misleading file path) would improve operational triage accuracy. This is a genuine code quality issue."},{"amendment_id":"fr-18-ffc497f2","decision":"reject","rationale":"The amendment's central claim — 'Issue 3 is still not implemented' — is factually incorrect. The test at lines 4727-4816 (plan_hash_auto_populated_from_snapshot) explicitly asserts that safe_plan_hash_backfill SUCCEEDS at completion time when snapshot provenance exists and hasn't evolved. The amendment mischaracterizes this test as asserting 'non-backfilling behavior.' For new entries: plan_hash is intentionally deferred from start to completion time due to the well-documented dispatch-v1/snapshot-v2 race condition, and backfill works correctly at completion. For legacy entries without provenance (test at 5392-5506): the deliberate skip is extensively documented inline with clear reasoning about correctness vs. completeness — this is a conscious safety choice, not a missing implementation. The amendment conflates two distinct scenarios and misreads the test evidence."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"e6363a63-1c27-43d1-a6a1-ee6d2cbc93be"}
